ean keep tabs on its position, why not?  It sounds like you need to factor your ‚Äúvisual tracking‚Äù away from your ‚Äúdrive tracking‚Äù so you can keep one going without affecting the other.<br>
According to <a href="http://motors.vex.com">motors.vex.com</a>, you can get up to 4.69 Nm, until you trip a breaker or melt something, which won‚Äôt take long.  More reasonably, you can get about 1Nm by setting a current limit of 60A.  Expect thermal shutdown in about 60 seconds.</p>","post_number":2,"post_type":1,"posts_count":8,"updated_at":"2022-02-28T22:34:20.865Z","reply_count":0,"reply_to_post_number":null,"quote_count":0,"incoming_link_count":1,"reads":159,"readers_count":158,"score":36.8,"yours":false,"topic_id":404235,"topic_slug":"help-with-tracking-and-moving-at-the-same-time","display_username":"Gus Michel II","primary_group_name":null,"flair_name":null,"flair_url":null,"flair_bg_color":null,"flair_color":null,"flair_group_id":null,"badges_granted":[],"version":2,"can_edit":false,"can_delete":false,"can_recover":false,"can_see_hidden_post":true,"can_wiki":false,"link_counts":[{"url":"http://motors.vex.com","internal":false,"reflection":false,"clicks":3}],"read":true,"user_title":"","bookmarked":false,"actions_summary":[],"moderator":false,"admin":false,"staff":false,"user_id":22335,"hidden":false,"trust_level":2,"deleted_at":null,"user_deleted":false,"edit_reason":null,"can_view_edit_history":true,"wiki":false,"user_custom_fields":{"user_field_4":"Somebody Else ‚¨õüü´üü•üüßüü®üü©üü¶üü™‚ñí‚ñí‚¨ú	"},"post_url":"/t/help-with-tracking-and-moving-at-the-same-time/404235/2","custom_user_title":"Somebody Else ‚¨õüü´üü•üüßüü®üü©üü¶üü™‚ñí‚ñí‚¨ú	","reactions":[],"current_user_reaction":null,"reaction_users_count":0,"current_user_used_main_reaction":false,"can_accept_answer":false,"can_unaccept_answer":false,"accepted_answer":false,"topic_accepted_answer":null},{"id":3014668,"name":"Nelson Green (1108 Mentor Coach Electrical Programming)","username":"ngreen","avatar_template":"/user_avatar/www.chiefdelphi.com/ngreen/{size}/264478_2.png","created_at":"2022-03-01T00:05:23.230Z","cooked":"<p>Our likely solution is to let the rotation of the robot track cargo and the driver control motion forward/backward.</p>
<p>This is all setup so that when the driver holds a button they have tracking on and when released it is manual driving.</p>","post_number":3,"post_type":1,"posts_count":8,"updated_at":"2022-03-01T00:05:23.230Z","reply_count":1,"reply_to_post_number":null,"quote_count":0,"incoming_link_count":1,"reads":136,"readers_count":135,"score":112.2,"yours":false,"topic_id":404235,"topic_slug":"help-with-tracking-and-moving-at-the-same-time","display_username":"Nelson Green (1108 Mentor Coach Electrical Programming)","primary_group_name":null,"flair_name":null,"flair_url":null,"flair_bg_color":null,"flair_color":null,"flair_group_id":null,"badges_granted":[],"version":1,"can_edit":false,"can_delete":false,"can_recover":false,"can_see_hidden_post":true,"can_wiki":false,"read":true,"user_title":"","bookmarked":false,"actions_summary":[{"id":2,"count":5}],"moderator":false,"admin":false,"staff":false,"user_id":2695,"hidden":false,"trust_level":2,"deleted_at":null,"user_deleted":false,"edit_reason":null,"can_view_edit_history":true,"wiki":false,"user_custom_fields":{"user_field_4":""},"post_url":"/t/help-with-tracking-and-moving-at-the-same-time/404235/3","custom_user_title":null,"reactions":[{"id":"heart","type":"emoji","count":5}],"current_user_reaction":null,"reaction_users_count":5,"current_user_used_main_reaction":false,"can_accept_answer":false,"can_unaccept_answer":false,"accepted_answer":false,"topic_accepted_answer":null},{"id":3015001,"name":"Justus","username":"Jus","avatar_template":"/user_avatar/www.chiefdelphi.com/jus/{size}/198009_2.png","created_at":"2022-03-01T17:03:42.792Z","cooked":"<p>Our idea is pretty much this, it takes control of the swervedrive rotation but leaves translation to drivers.</p>","post_number":4,"post_type":1,"posts_count":8,"updated_at":"2022-03-01T17:03:42.792Z","reply_count":1,"reply_to_post_number":3,"quote_count":0,"incoming_link_count":2,"reads":106,"readers_count":105,"score":96.2,"yours":false,"topic_id":404235,"topic_slug":"help-with-tracking-and-moving-at-the-same-time","display_username":"Justus","primary_group_name":null,"flair_name":null,"flair_url":null,"flair_bg_color":null,"flair_color":null,"flair_group_id":null,"badges_granted":[],"version":1,"can_edit":false,"can_delete":false,"can_recover":false,"can_see_hidden_post":true,"can_wiki":false,"read":true,"user_title":"","reply_to_user":{"id":2695,"username":"ngreen","name":"Nelson Green (1108 Mentor Coach Electrical Programming)","avatar_template":"/user_avatar/www.chiefdelphi.com/ngreen/{size}/264478_2.png"},"bookmarked":false,"actions_summary":[{"id":2,"count":4}],"moderator":false,"admin":false,"staff":false,"user_id":49388,"hidden":false,"trust_level":2,"deleted_at":null,"user_deleted":false,"edit_reason":null,"can_view_edit_history":true,"wiki":false,"user_custom_fields":{"user_field_4":"Microsoft"},"post_url":"/t/help-with-tracking-and-moving-at-the-same-time/404235/4","custom_user_title":"Microsoft","reactions":[{"id":"heart","type":"emoji","count":4}],"current_user_reaction":null,"reaction_users_count":4,"current_user_used_main_reaction":false,"can_accept_answer":false,"can_unaccept_answer":false,"accepted_answer":false,"topic_accepted_answer":null},{"id":3015306,"name":"","username":"kiwi0401","avatar_template":"/letter_avatar_proxy/v4/letter/k/5f9b8f/{size}.png","created_at":"2022-03-02T01:03:36.221Z","cooked":"<pre><code>    private double getRotationSpeed() {
    if (MathUtil.isWithinTolerance(Gyro.getInstance().getRotation2d().getDegrees(), driveTrain.getTargetRotationAngle(), 2.5)) {
        return 0.0;
    }
    double vel = (0.025 * (driveTrain.getTargetRotationAngle() - Gyro.getInstance().getRotation2d().getDegrees()));
    if (Math.abs(vel) &lt; MIN_VEL) {
        vel = Math.signum(vel) * MIN_VEL;
    }
    return Math.signum(vel) * Math.min(Math.abs(vel), MAX_TURN_SPEED);
}
</code></pre>
<p>We‚Äôve used this code with our swerve controls with a lot of success. We just keep a target rotation in drivetrain and any command can kinda just set it at will and our DT will angle towards wherever. This has the benefits that the driver can still drive and rotate the robot like they normally would</p>
<pre><code>         var leftJoystick = ControlMap.DRIVER_LEFT;
    var rightJoystick = ControlMap.DRIVER_RIGHT;
    var xSpeed = MathUtil.fitDeadband(-leftJoystick.getY()) * DriveTrain.MAX_SPEED;
    var ySpeed = MathUtil.fitDeadband(-leftJoystick.getX()) * DriveTrain.MAX_SPEED;

    var rot = MathUtil.fitDeadband(rightJoystick.getX()) * DriveTrain.MAX_ANGULAR_SPEED;

    if (rot == 0) {
        driveTrain.drive(xSpeed, ySpeed, getRotationSpeed(), driveTrain.getFieldCentric());
    } else {
        driveTrain.setTargetRotationAngle(Gyro.getInstance().getRotation2d().getDegrees());
        driveTrain.drive(xSpeed, ySpeed, rot, driveTrain.getFieldCentric());
    }</code></pre>","post_number":5,"post_type":1,"posts_count":8,"updated_at":"2022-03-02T01:03:36.221Z","reply_count":1,"reply_to_post_number":4,"quote_count":0,"incoming_link_count":4,"reads":76,"readers_count":75,"score":40.2,"yours":false,"topic_id":404235,"topic_slug":"help-with-tracking-and-moving-at-the-same-time","display_username":"","primary_group_name":null,"flair_name":null,"flair_url":null,"flair_bg_color":null,"flair_color":null,"flair_group_id":null,"badges_granted":[],"version":1,"can_edit":false,"can_delete":false,"can_recover":false,"can_see_hidden_post":true,"can_wiki":false,"read":true,"user_title":null,"reply_to_user":{"id":49388,"username":"Jus","name":"Justus","avatar_template":"/user_avatar/www.chiefdelphi.com/jus/{size}/198009_2.png"},"bookmarked":false,"actions_summary":[],"moderator":false,"admin":false,"staff":false,"user_id":50646,"hidden":false,"trust_level":2,"deleted_at":null,"user_deleted":false,"edit_reason":null,"can_view_edit_history":true,"wiki":false,"user_custom_fields":{"user_field_4":"5818 - Coding Mentor"},"post_url":"/t/help-with-tracking-and-moving-at-the-same-time/404235/5","custom_user_title":"5818 - Coding Mentor","reactions":[],"current_user_reaction":null,"reaction_users_count":0,"current_user_used_main_reaction":false,"can_accept_answer":false,"can_unaccept_answer":false,"accepted_answer":false,"topic_accepted_answer":null},{"id":3015397,"name":"Justus","username":"Jus","avatar_template":"/user_avatar/www.chiefdelphi.com/jus/{size}/198009_2.png","created_at":"2022-03-02T03:23:35.543Z","cooked":"<p>When you are pressing the button that aligns your rotation, override <code>rot</code> with the output of a tuned PID which uses pixel x coordinate from your video system as input.</p>","post_number":6,"post_type":1,"posts_count":8,"updated_at":"2022-03-02T03:23:35.543Z","reply_count":1,"reply_to_post_number":5,"quote_count":0,"incoming_link_count":2,"reads":56,"readers_count":55,"score":26.2,"yours":false,"topic_id":404235